threads.title: 820-00165 no power - liquid damaged
threads.message:
This board was taken somewhere else for repair, looks like they cleaned it but no board repair was done, i have tested power aliases to see, but im stuck here, also test short to ground on missing power aliases and got no shorts, did not do ohms to ground, ( i know i should have not posted S4, S3 AND S0 if S5 was missing, but i have a template written out to help me remember all power aliases to look at on each board,)

need some help here, any help is appreciated where to go from here. 

Thanks in advance



PPBUS_G3H - 8 6V

PP3V42_G3H - 3.42V

PPBUS_S5_HS_COMPUTING ISNS - 8 6V

PPBUS_S5_HS_OTHER ISNS - 8 6V

PPDCIN_G3H - 3.42V

PP5V_S5 - 5V

PP5V_S4RS3 - 0.0V TO 0.6V back to 0.0V

PP5V_S0 - 0V

PP3V3_S5 - 3.3V

PP3V3_S4 - 0.0V TO 0.2V then back 0.0V

PP3V3_SUS - 0V

PP3V3_S3 - 0V

PP3V3_S0 - 0V

PP1V8_S3 - 0V

PP1V2_S3 - 0V



SMC_BC_ACOK - 3.3V

threads.title: 820-00165 no power - liquid damaged
threads.message:
Missing PM_SLP_SUS_L?

Post PM_RSMRST_L, PM_PWRBTN_L, PM_BATLOW_L, PM_DSW_PWRGD. PCH_DSWVRMEN.
Also check all 4 PCH's RTC signals; page 12, U0500 (SYM 5 OF 19).

threads.title: 820-00165 no power - liquid damaged
threads.message:
PM_SLP_SUS_L - 0v

PM_RSMRST_L - 0V

PM_PWRBTN_L - 3.4V

PM_BATLOW_L - 3.33V

PM_DSW_PWRGD - 0V

PCH_DSWVRMEN - 3.23V



PCH INTRUDER L - 3.05V

PCH_INTVRMEN - 3.24V

PCH_SRTCRST_L - 3.3

RTC RESET L - 3.3V

threads.title: 820-00165 no power - liquid damaged
threads.message:
S5_PWRGD is there?
If missing, check R8141.
If present, SMC issue.

Also check SMC_S5_PWRGD_VIN and R5192.
